Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows mild normocytic anemia (low hemoglobin), hyperglycemia with normal HbA1c (possible stress or acute glucose elevation), dyslipidemia (high total cholesterol, LDL, triglycerides, low HDL), and elevated iron saturation. Cardiac markers (NT-proBNP, troponin) are within or near normal limits for age. Renal and liver function are unremarkable. Recommend further evaluation of anemia, glucose control, and cardiovascular risk management.
